Rating: 4
This recipe has become a summer time tradition for us. I use chicken breasts instead of thighs, and we add vidalia onion and sweet bell peppers. I omit the bacon and add feta cheese to the pita bread. It is always a big hit! I'm sure I will continue to make it again and again.

Rating: 4
The marinade IS wonderful since it really flavors the chicken after half an hour. In an attempt to cut calories, I omitted bacon but used Creamy Dill Dressing from this site. I also did not make kebabs but sliced chicken breasts horizontally to make them cook fast,fit in the pita better, and have better exposure to the marinade. I think the sandwiches would be too dry with just the poultry and mushroom mixture with or without bacon. Thanks to reviewers who alerted me to use a dressing. If you are out of cucumber, tomato, and other types of bread, this recipe will serve you well.

Rating: 3
I made this for a party and it was a big hit. I took the suggestions and made the dill sauce. I also served it with flat bread instead of pita bread (flat bread is delicious and more moist). The mushrooms were incredible.

Rating: 2
